---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Privacy Policy"
	description="Privacy Policy for True Recall — how we collect, use, and protect your data."
>
	<div class="legal-page">
		<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
		<p class="meta">Effective date: March 22, 2026 · Last updated: March 29, 2026</p>

		<p>
			This Privacy Policy explains how True Recall ("<strong>we</strong>", "<strong>us</strong>",
			"<strong>our</strong>") collects, uses, and protects information about you when you use our
			website at <a href="https://truerecall.app">truerecall.app</a> and the True Recall Obsidian
			plugin (collectively, the "<strong>Service</strong>").
		</p>

		<h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
		<p>
			The data controller responsible for your personal data is:<br />
			<strong>Łukasz Piera</strong>, operating under the name True Recall, based in Poland.<br />
			For all data-related enquiries, including GDPR requests, contact us at:
			<a href="mailto:pieralukasz@gmail.com">pieralukasz@gmail.com</a>.
		</p>

		<h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
		<p>We collect only what is necessary to provide the Service.</p>

		<h3>Account data</h3>
		<p>
			When you register or log in, we collect your <strong>email address</strong>. We use Supabase
			magic-link authentication — no password is stored.
		</p>

		<h3>Usage data</h3>
		<p>
			We store your AI generation count and subscription tier in our database. This is required to
			enforce plan limits (Free Trial, Pro) and display your usage on the dashboard.
		</p>

		<h3>Payment data</h3>
		<p>
			Payments are processed by <a href="https://polar.sh" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Polar</a>.
			We do <em>not</em> store card numbers or full billing details. We receive only a customer
			identifier, subscription status, and purchase history sufficient to manage your account.
		</p>

		<h3>Analytics data</h3>
		<p>
			We use <strong>Vercel Analytics</strong> to collect anonymous, aggregated page-view
			statistics (pages visited, country, browser type). No cookies are set by True Recall for
			analytics purposes; Vercel Analytics operates without cookies and without collecting personal
			identifiers.
		</p>

		<h3>AI processing data</h3>
		<p>
			True Recall acts solely as an intermediary for AI features. When you use AI functionality,
			your content is passed through to third-party AI providers via
			<a href="https://openrouter.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenRouter</a>. We do not
			store, retain, or have ongoing access to the content you submit. The text and images you
			provide remain yours at all times — we merely transmit them on your behalf. True Recall has
			<strong>prompt logging disabled</strong> at OpenRouter.
		</p>
		<p>The following AI features involve data transmission:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<strong>AI Flashcard Generation</strong> — text snippets you select in your notes are
				sent to OpenRouter for flashcard creation.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Image Occlusion (AI Detect)</strong> — images you select from your vault are
				sent to OpenRouter for region detection and analysis. Images may contain sensitive
				information such as photographs of individuals, identity documents, or medical diagrams.
				You are solely responsible for the content of images you submit.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Type-in Grading</strong> — when enabled, your typed answer and the expected
				answer are sent to an AI model for semantic similarity evaluation.
			</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			All AI features are user-initiated — data is never sent to AI providers automatically or in
			the background. True Recall does not use your content to train AI models. However, the
			underlying LLM providers may have their own data retention policies; see
			<a href="https://openrouter.ai/docs/guides/privacy/logging" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
				>OpenRouter's provider logging documentation</a
			> for details.
		</p>

		<h3>Data you create in the plugin</h3>
		<p>
			Flashcard content (questions, answers, notes) is stored entirely on your own device inside
			your Obsidian vault. It is <em>not</em> transmitted to our servers unless you explicitly
			enable Cloud Sync.
		</p>
		<p>
			<strong>Cloud Sync (when enabled):</strong> If you enable Cloud Sync, flashcard content,
			review history, and scheduling data are transmitted to and stored on Supabase servers in the
			EU (AWS eu-central-1). Sync is entirely opt-in and can be disabled at any time. Your data
			remains yours — we store it solely to provide the synchronisation service.
		</p>
		<p>
			<strong>MCP Server:</strong> The True Recall MCP Server exposes plugin tools on
			<code>localhost</code> only (127.0.0.1). No data is sent to external servers by the MCP
			Server itself. Third-party MCP clients you connect may transmit data according to their own
			policies; you are responsible for which clients you connect.
		</p>

		<h3>Bring Your Own Key (BYOK)</h3>
		<p>
			When you configure your own OpenRouter API key, AI requests are sent directly under your
			OpenRouter account. <a href="https://openrouter.ai/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
				>OpenRouter's privacy policy</a
			> governs that data relationship. True Recall has no visibility into or control over
			prompts processed through your own key and does not track your BYOK usage.
		</p>

		<h2>3. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
		<p>We rely on the following legal bases under GDPR Article 6:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<strong>Contract performance (Art. 6(1)(b))</strong> — processing your email address and
				usage data is necessary to create and manage your account and deliver the Service.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Consent (Art. 6(1)(a))</strong> — where you explicitly choose to send content
				(including images that may contain personal data) to AI providers via the Service's AI
				features.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Legitimate interests (Art. 6(1)(f))</strong> — anonymous analytics help us
				understand how the Service is used and improve it. This interest does not override your
				rights.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Legal obligation (Art. 6(1)(c))</strong> — we may process data where required by
				applicable law (e.g. keeping records for tax purposes).
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>4. Special Categories of Data (Art. 9 GDPR)</h2>
		<p>
			True Recall does not intentionally collect special category data as defined by GDPR
			Article 9 (data revealing racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious beliefs,
			health data, biometric data, etc.).
		</p>
		<p>
			However, content you create or submit — such as medical flashcards, photographs of
			individuals, or images of identity documents — may contain special category or sensitive
			personal data. When you send such content to AI providers via the Service's AI features,
			you act as the data controller for that data and are responsible for ensuring you have a
			lawful basis for processing it.
		</p>
		<p>
			<strong>Do not submit personal data of third parties</strong> (such as photographs,
			identity documents, health records, or biometric data) to AI features unless you have a
			lawful basis and, where required, their explicit consent. True Recall acts solely as an
			intermediary and does not review, store, or moderate the content you pass through to AI
			providers.
		</p>

		<h2>5. Third-Party Data Processors</h2>
		<p>
			We share your data only with the processors listed below, each bound by appropriate data
			processing agreements and GDPR-compliant safeguards.
		</p>
		<table>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th>Processor</th>
					<th>Purpose</th>
					<th>Location</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tbody>
				<tr>
					<td><a href="https://supabase.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Supabase</a></td>
					<td>Authentication, database storage, Cloud Sync</td>
					<td>EU (AWS eu-central-1)</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><a href="https://openrouter.ai/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenRouter</a></td>
					<td>AI model routing (text and image processing)</td>
					<td>USA (SCCs apply)</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><a href="https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Vercel</a></td>
					<td>Hosting, anonymous analytics</td>
					<td>USA (SCCs apply)</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><a href="https://resend.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Resend</a></td>
					<td>Transactional emails (magic link, waitlist)</td>
					<td>USA (SCCs apply)</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><a href="https://polar.sh/legal/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Polar</a></td>
					<td>Payment processing, subscription management</td>
					<td>USA (SCCs apply)</td>
				</tr>
			</tbody>
		</table>
		<p>
			We will notify you by email at least <strong>30 days</strong> before engaging a new
			sub-processor or making a material change to an existing one. If you object, you may
			terminate your account before the change takes effect.
		</p>

		<h2>6. International Data Transfers</h2>
		<p>
			All account and Cloud Sync data stored by Supabase resides in the EU (AWS eu-central-1).
		</p>
		<p>
			Data sent to OpenRouter, Vercel, Resend, and Polar is transferred to the United States
			under Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) approved by the European Commission
			(Decision 2021/914), together with supplementary measures where appropriate per EDPB
			recommendations.
		</p>
		<p>
			For AI features specifically, OpenRouter routes requests to third-party LLM providers
			(such as Anthropic, OpenAI, and others) that may be located in various jurisdictions.
			True Recall has prompt logging disabled on OpenRouter, but cannot control the data
			practices of individual LLM providers.
		</p>

		<h2>7. Data Security</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>All communications between the plugin, our website, and third-party processors use
				<strong>TLS encryption</strong> in transit.</li>
			<li>Supabase provides <strong>encryption at rest</strong> for all stored data.</li>
			<li>Your local SQLite database (<code>.true-recall/</code>) is stored unencrypted on your
				device. You are responsible for device-level encryption (e.g. FileVault, BitLocker).</li>
			<li>Access to production systems is restricted to the data controller (sole operator).
				There are no employees with access to user data.</li>
			<li>We regularly review the security practices and certifications of our third-party
				processors.</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>8. Data Breach Notification</h2>
		<p>
			In the event of a personal data breach, we will notify the relevant supervisory authority
			(UODO) within <strong>72 hours</strong> of becoming aware, as required by GDPR Article 33.
		</p>
		<p>
			If the breach is likely to result in a high risk to your rights and freedoms, we will
			notify you without undue delay by email at the address associated with your account
			(GDPR Article 34).
		</p>

		<h2>9. Data Retention</h2>
		<p>
			We retain your account data for as long as your account is active. If you request account
			deletion, we will delete your personal data within <strong>30 days</strong>, except where
			retention is required by law (e.g. transaction records for 5 years under Polish accounting
			law). Anonymised or aggregated data may be retained indefinitely.
		</p>
		<p>
			<strong>AI processing data:</strong> True Recall does not retain any content you submit to
			AI features. We act as a pass-through intermediary only. Retention by OpenRouter and
			underlying LLM providers is governed by their respective privacy policies.
		</p>
		<p>
			<strong>Cloud Sync data:</strong> Retained as long as your account is active and sync is
			enabled. Deleted within 30 days of account deletion or sync disablement.
		</p>

		<h2>10. AI Transparency (EU AI Act)</h2>
		<p>
			In accordance with the EU AI Act (Regulation 2024/1689), we provide the following
			transparency information about AI systems used within the Service:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<strong>Purpose:</strong> AI is used for (a) flashcard generation from text,
				(b) image analysis for Image Occlusion region detection, and (c) semantic answer
				evaluation for Type-in Grading. These are classified as limited-risk AI applications.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Intermediary role:</strong> True Recall does not train, fine-tune, or host any
				AI models. We act solely as an intermediary, passing your content to third-party models
				via OpenRouter and returning the results to you.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Labelling:</strong> All AI-generated content is clearly identified as
				machine-generated within the plugin interface.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Non-exclusivity:</strong> AI-generated outputs (such as flashcards) are produced
				by third-party models and may be similar or identical to outputs generated for other
				users. No exclusive rights to any particular AI output are granted.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Human review:</strong> You may disable AI grading at any time and use manual
				grading instead. No consequential decisions are made solely by AI — all AI outputs are
				assistive and can be reviewed, edited, or discarded.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Data minimization:</strong> Only the minimum necessary text or image is sent to
				AI providers. Your full vault contents are never transmitted.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>No training:</strong> True Recall does not use your content to train, or allow
				any third party to train, any AI models.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>11. Your Rights Under GDPR</h2>
		<p>
			If you are located in the EU/EEA, you have the following rights regarding your personal data:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Right of access</strong> — obtain a copy of the data we hold about you.</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Right to rectification</strong> — correct inaccurate or incomplete data.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Right to erasure ("right to be forgotten")</strong> — request deletion of your
				data, subject to legal retention requirements.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Right to restrict processing</strong> — limit how we use your data in certain
				circumstances.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Right to data portability</strong> — receive your data in a structured,
				machine-readable format.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Right to object</strong> — object to processing based on legitimate interests.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Rights related to automated decision-making</strong> — True Recall uses AI for
				flashcard generation and answer grading, but these do not constitute automated
				decision-making with legal or similarly significant effects. You can disable AI grading
				at any time and review all generated content manually.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Right to lodge a complaint</strong> — you may file a complaint with the Polish
				Data Protection Authority (<a
					href="https://uodo.gov.pl"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener">UODO</a
				>) or the supervisory authority in your country of residence.
			</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			To exercise any of these rights, email us at <a href="mailto:pieralukasz@gmail.com"
				>pieralukasz@gmail.com</a
			>. We will respond within 30 days.
		</p>

		<h2>12. Cookies</h2>
		<p>
			True Recall does not set tracking or analytics cookies. Supabase sets a session cookie
			strictly necessary for authentication. You cannot opt out of this cookie without losing the
			ability to log in.
		</p>

		<h2>13. Children's Privacy</h2>
		<p>
			The Service is not directed at children under the age of 16. We do not knowingly collect
			personal data from anyone under 16. If you believe a child has provided us with their data,
			contact us and we will delete it promptly.
		</p>

		<h2>14. Changes to This Policy</h2>
		<p>
			We may update this Privacy Policy. For material changes, we will notify you by email (at the
			address associated with your account) at least 14 days before the change takes effect. The
			date at the top of this page always reflects the latest revision.
		</p>

		<h2>15. Contact</h2>
		<p>
			Questions about this policy or your data? Email us at <a href="mailto:pieralukasz@gmail.com"
				>pieralukasz@gmail.com</a
			>.
		</p>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.legal-page {
		max-width: 760px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding-top: 2.5rem;
		padding-bottom: 4rem;
	}

	.legal-page h1 {
		font-size: 2rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
	}

	.meta {
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-4);
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}

	.legal-page h2 {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		margin-top: 2.25rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.625rem;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-1);
	}

	.legal-page h3 {
		font-size: 1rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin-top: 1.25rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
	}

	.legal-page p,
	.legal-page li {
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
		line-height: 1.7;
		font-size: 0.9375rem;
	}

	.legal-page p + p {
		margin-top: 0.75rem;
	}

	.legal-page ul {
		margin: 0.625rem 0 0.625rem 1.25rem;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.375rem;
	}

	.legal-page a {
		color: var(--sl-color-accent-high);
	}

	table {
		width: 100%;
		border-collapse: collapse;
		margin: 1rem 0;
		font-size: 0.875rem;
	}

	th,
	td {
		text-align: left;
		padding: 0.625rem 0.75rem;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5);
	}

	th {
		background: var(--sl-color-gray-6);
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	td {
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
	}
</style>
